<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>There are many ways to qualify for the Confederation of African Football (Caf) competitions.A team can book their spot in the lucrative Champions League if they secure the top two positions on the log table.Finishing third on the table guarantees a team a spot in the Confederation Cup. The team that win the Nedbank Cup automatically qualify for the Confederation Cup preliminary stages.Winning the Nedbank Cup will see Bucs seal their passage to the Confederation Cup. Bucs Serbian coach, Milutin Sredojevic, has expressed the club’s strong desire to get back to African football.The Serbian, who has travelled across Africa coaching several teams, knows that his wish can come true if they win the cup or secure a top three position on the log table.Sredojevic said: “Despite coming from Europe, I regard myself as an African coach because Africa has given everything to me.“In that regard, I want to take Pirates and South African football to African football to showcase the brand that we’re carrying.“It’s our ultimate target to play in the Champions League or the Confederation Cup in order to keep up with other big clubs on the continent. This club belong in continental football and we want to see ourselves up there with the big names next season.”Before their home game against Polokwane City at the Orlando Stadium last night, Sredojevic’s charges had won their first two league games of the new year. The outspoken Serbian said despite being on the continent for many years, he was still learning and hoped to become a top coach.Sredojevic said: “Over the 25 years of coaching I’m learning every day. I want to move Mzansi football to the next level and to achieve that we want to play attractive football.“We want a competitive squad to deal with issues of fatigue when we go to Caf competitions.”Sredojevic added that he was happy with the depth of his squad as he embarked on his goal of qualifying for the Caf competitions next season.